2 Analaysis summary

We conducted a literature review using the web of science citation system (search query: https://www.webofscience.com/wos/woscc/summary/7f060455-0bd6-4643-bd2f-2de3ceedb0b2-f52da389/relevance/1). To be included in this analysis, each paper had to contain a long-term fisheries survey or pilot study of a new study Our search returned 1,803 entries, of which contained 2 duplicate results and 361 irrelevant results, leaving 95 relevant articles to categorize. The following categories were used in this analysis:

Gear Type: 3D stereo camera (e.g., stereo-baited remote underwater video (S-BRUV)), Acoustics, Advanced Tech, Beach seine, Beam Trawl, Bongo net, Bottom Trawl, Fisher interviews, Fisheries-Dependant, Gillnets, Grab samples, Hook & Line, Ichthyoplankton, Longline, Multiple, None, Otter Trawl, Pelagic net, Poly Nor’Eastern, four-seam, hard bottom, high-rise bottom trawl (AFSC BTS AI & GOA), Stock assessments, Traps, Uncrewed surface vehicle saildrone, Video

Research topic: Bycatch, Catchability, Climate change, Combine Surveys, Combine with Dependant, Data availability, Design-based indicies, Ecosystem-based management, Editorial, Emerging Methods, Essential Fish Habitat, Food web model, Harvest Control Rules, Histology, Life History, Model-Based Indicies, MPA, Oceanography, Otolith, Outreach and Communication, Population Model, Recruitment, Reference points, Review, Sampling design, Socio-Econ, Species Distribution Model, Stock Assessment Model, Survey Design, Survey Mitigation, Survey Statistics, Uncertainty, Wind Farm mitigation

Location: Adriatic Sea, Arafura Sea, Azores, Baltic Sea, Barents Sea, Brazil, Caribbean, Celtic Sea, China, Coral Sea, Eastern Indian Ocean, English Channel, Global, Great Australian Bight, Greater North Sea, Gulf of Mexico, Hawaii, Iberian Coast, Mediterranean Sea, Mid-NW Atlantic, NE Atlantic, NE Pacific, NW Atlantic, Pacific West Coast, Russia, Simulation, South-NW Atlantic, South Africa, Southern Ocean, Tasman Sea

Survey: ADFG - Southeast AK Sabelfish Longline Assessment; AFSC ATS - eastern Bering Sea; AFSC BTS - Aleutian Islands; AFSC BTS - Bering Sea Slope; AFSC BTS - eastern Bering Sea; AFSC BTS - Gulf of Alaska; AFSC BTS - northern Bering Sea; AFSC EcoFOCI ichthyoplankton survey - eastern Bering Sea; AFSC Observer; Azorean bottom longline survey; Baltic International Trawl Survey; BASS - hydroacoustic surveys Baltic Acoustic Spring Survey; BIAS - Baltic International Acoustic Survey; BITS - Baltic International Trawl Survey; Brazil longline survey; CA Pelagic shark longline survey; CalCOFI; CCES - SWFSC nearshore acoustics California Current Ecosystem Survey; Channel Ground Fish Survey; China - East China Sea; China - Haizhou Bay; China - Shandong Peninsula; China - Yangtze River estuary; CSIRO; DFO BTS - Scotian Shelf summer bottom trawl survey; Europe; Georgia Department of Natural Resources’ Coastal Resources Division has used a stratified; Greater North Sea International Otter Trawl Survey; ICES Beam Trawl Survey; ICES UK - International Bottom Trawl Survey; IPHC - Halibut Longline Assessment; MARMAP - Chevron Trap Survey; MARMAP - various gear; MEDITS - EU-funded MEDIterranean Trawl Survey; NEFSC BTS; NEFSC Gulf of Maine Bottom Longline Survey; NEPTUNE cabled observatory; NMFS COASTSPAN Apex Predator Investigation; NMFS SEAMAP Reef Fish Video Survey, the NMFS Panama City (Florida) survey, and the Fish and Wildlife Research Institute of the Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission survey; Northern Ireland Ground Fish Survey; NWFSC BTS; NWFSC DFO ATS Hake; NWFSC Observer; PRS - NWFSC coastal cooperative pre-recruit survey; Queensland scallop survey; RREAS - SWFSC Rockfish Recruitment and Ecosystem Assessment Survey; SEAMAP; SERFS - Southeast Reef Fish Survey; SESSF; Simulation; Study; TINRO; TPWD - Texas Parks and Wildlife Department
